# <name> — Flutter runtime check

A runnable scaffold for a project-authored verification skill that drives the
**running Flutter app** (not just unit/widget tests) and asserts the real user
journey end-to-end. Modeled on a `glacy-drive`-style skill: connect to the live
app, read the widget tree, tap and type, then confirm the expected screen with
no runtime errors.

> Read the authoring guide — `docs/verification-skills.md` — before filling this
> in. It explains how `verify_skill` wires this skill into the `## Verification`
> hook and how the disable-model-invocation marker keeps it opt-in.

## What this checks

The end-to-end runtime journey a user actually walks through, exercised against
the app running on a real device or simulator. Deterministic gates (analyzer,
`flutter test`) still run first and always win; this check adds the runtime
behavior those gates cannot see.

